@startuml seq_health_observer
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam sequence {
    ArrowColor #737266
    ArrowFontColor #444444
    ArrowFontSize 12
    LifeLineBorderColor #AAAAAA
    ParticipantBorderColor #534AB7
    ParticipantBackgroundColor #EEEDFE
    ParticipantFontColor #3C3489
    BoxBorderColor #B07D00
    BoxBackgroundColor #FFF9E6
    NoteBackgroundColor #F5F5FF
    NoteBorderColor #9B94E0
}
skinparam roundcorner 6

title Approval Controller — Health Observer\n(runs on every reconcile pass, across all ProvisionedResources)

box "Management Cluster" #FFF9E6
    participant "ResourceRequest\nReconciler" as REC
    participant "Health\nObserver" as HO
    participant "ProvisionedResource\nCRD" as PRCRD #E8F4FD
end box

box "Target Cluster  (via Rancher, controller SA)" #FFF3CD
    participant "CRD Target\nInstance" as CTI
end box

note over REC, PRCRD
  The Health Observer is invoked on every reconcile pass —
  including periodic resyncs — not only when a ResourceRequest
  event triggers reconciliation. It operates independently of
  the Provisioning State Machine and reads all ProvisionedResource
  objects in ''provisioned'' or ''updating'' phase from the
  controller's own cache.
end note

== Per-ProvisionedResource health check ==

REC -> HO    : runHealthObserver()
HO  -> PRCRD : list ProvisionedResources\n[phase: provisioned | updating]
PRCRD --> HO : list of objects

loop for each ProvisionedResource

    HO -> CTI : get status.conditions\n[controller SA, read-only]

    group Case 1 — Ready: no change required
        CTI --> HO : Ready = True
        note over HO : ProvisionedResource.status.phase\nalready reflects healthy state;\nno write needed
    end

    group Case 2 — NotReady: surface degraded status
        CTI --> HO : Ready = False
        HO  -> PRCRD : patch status.phase = degraded\n[status subresource write only]
        note over PRCRD : Degraded status surfaced in the portal\nvia Web App informer cache.\nNo ResourceRequest created.
    end

    group Case 3 — NotFound + ProvisionedResource NOT in ''deleting'' phase
        CTI --> HO : NotFound
        note over HO : CRD target instance deleted out-of-band\n(not through a portal delete request).\nRe-applying to restore desired state.

        HO  -> PRCRD : patch status.phase = unknown
        HO  -> CTI   : SSA apply CRD target instance\n[controller SA — restores from\nProvisionedResource.spec.appliedParameters]

        note over HO, CTI
          AUDIT TRADE-OFF: This re-apply bypasses the
          approval workflow and produces no ResourceRequest
          audit trail entry. Operators who require an audit
          trail for all target-cluster writes should disable
          this behaviour and instead alert on status.phase = unknown,
          treating out-of-band deletion as a manual incident.
        end note

        CTI --> HO : accepted
        note over HO : Readiness of the re-applied instance\nwill be observed on the next reconcile pass.\nProvisionedResource status.phase remains\n''unknown'' until Ready is confirmed.
    end

    group Case 4 — NotFound + ProvisionedResource in ''deleting'' phase
        CTI --> HO : NotFound
        note over HO : Deletion in progress via a portal\ndelete request — handled by the\nProvisioning Handler. Health Observer skips.
    end

end

REC <-- HO : done

@enduml
